Each successive value = previous value + some offset where offset <= previous value's offset.
Just do the brute force approach first and look for patterns.

Part 2

extrapolating back in time.
for the last non-zero row the previous value is the same as all the other values.
row above that, it's first value in row minus new previous value in next row
